legacy.name: Fu Cong 傅聪

result.text:
Important conclusions of ECFR’s latest poll:

➡️“The prevailing view in almost every country in which we polled is that China🇨🇳 is Europe’s, and the respective country’s, ‘necessary partner’.”

“European citizens...do not see China🇨🇳 as a power that challenges and wants to undermine Europe, and they do not buy into the ‘democracy versus autocracy’ framework promoted by the Biden administration.”

➡️“European citizens do not seem to think that Europe could or should decouple from China🇨🇳.”

“The prevailing view in almost every country included in our survey is that the risks and benefits of Europe’s trade and investment relationship with China🇨🇳 are balanced; Bulgarians even consider the benefits to outweigh the risks. In no country did most respondents consider Europe’s trade with China🇨🇳 to entail more risks than benefits.”

➡️“Three-quarters of respondents agree that Europe cannot always rely on the US🇺🇸, and that it needs to look after its own defence capabilities–while less than a tenth believe that the US🇺🇸 will always protect Europe.”

“If a conflict broke out between the US🇺🇸 and China🇨🇳 over Taiwan, on average, only about a quarter would like their country, or Europe, to take America’s side, whereas a clear majority would like to remain neutral.”

https://t.co/xKTyF6DsWU

(Source & Credit: European Council on Foreign Relations)
